Ok, pulid, just to clarify. I'm assuming you're speaking of the third book of the lord of the rings. Nearing the end, Frodo and Sam eventually destroyed the One Ring. It held Sauron's power, blah blah blah, and in that power was the control he had over his thousands of minions (including orcs). When the ring gets destroyed, the power dissappears with it, and therefore all his minions just go freaking crazy running around and killing just about anything.<br>
<br>
I really doubt an orc would kill another orc any more than a human would kill another human. Heh =P<br>
