<br>
Overall Standings<br>
Neutral Alliance 1,351,334 points<br>
Good Alliance 740,020 points<br>
Evil Alliance 673,529 points &quot;<br>
<br>
Actually, they're losing &quot;because&quot; there's so many of them.  If you had a 40, 30, 30 split or something more even (while still out numbering) evil could be higher in the standing.  But when you run around the world of Norrath, and come across mostly evils... there's nothing to kill.  Much harder for the evils to find something else that's not also evil... where as the good or newt teams can't throw a stone without hitting an evil.  They have a much much larger pool of characters to select from to kill.  They will never run out of targets.  The evil team on the other hand has to search to find their targets a bit more.<br>
<br>
Same concept as in Quake, or any other FPS for that matter.  The worst thing you could possibly do is team up on someone.  You've significally shrunk your possible targets for  gaining points, but doubled, tripled, even quaded &quot;their's&quot; depending on how badly you outnumber them.<br>
<br>
